CHERI | @babynurse81 in her own words: “Being a full time Nurse, a wife and a mother to 5 kids its easy to loose yourself in everyday life. This past 2 years have been hard mentally and emotionally for me. I had injured my back I have a tear and a herniated disk causing me to stop going to the gym. My daughter was diagnosed with Lupus and 6 months later my son was diagnosed with Autism spectrum disorder. I become pregnant with baby #5 put on bed rest at 22 weeks...and then Covid hit hard. Canada shutdown completely . Baby was born healthy little girl and the doctors appointments seemed endless for my other 2 children. The weight just keep piling on. The back pain was so bad I knew I needed to look after me so I could look after my children. I have followed Lauren for awhile now and knew we have the same drive ! It was no question I wanted to do her program and see what I could accomplish. I got up earlier then everyone in the house to get in the workouts . I just got into this zone and pushed hard every time. I followed Lauren's plan and the results speak for themselves! Stared at 170.8 now 148.8 and down 20.6 inches and feeling GREAT! I'm ready for the next challenge to push even harder!! Anyone thinking about should they do it?? I say DO IT! You won't regret it. Thank you Lauren for keeping me consistent and pushing even on days I didn't think I could.” She also took home $1,000 in cash! Join my next 6 Week Challenge starting next Sunday July 25th. Spots are filling up fast. Get all the info via the link in my bio💪🏽 Spots are almost gone so get yours while you still can🙈 What are you waiting for? If you are hesitant just look over the testimonials on my website or drop me an email with your questions. node.text: I’m sure Ive missed a few but here are some of my favorite pics and videos of @theiobot being an amazing father. We love you so much it honestly hurts. We’re so happy you’re here, you love us, you give your all and you love Aria so much it truly astonishes me every day. I’ve never been more attracted and in love with @theiobot than now seeing you raise our little angel to be safe, happy, loved, protected, be given such an amazing example of how to be a good human. She adores you so much. I thought it might make me jealous lol but honestly daily seeing her reach for you, cry when you leave the room and instantly stop crying when you pop her up on your shoulders, gives me so much peace, joy, happiness and fills my heart which was once so empty with love. Thank you, Daddy. We could never tell you how much we need you and love you. Thank you for choosing to be with us and being the best version of yourself for us 🥰❤️👨‍👩‍👧 @theiobot @ariaskyekagan

node.text:
TAG A FRIEND who needs motivation! 🙌🏼 Let's be real for a second, none of this perfect fitness model crap 😂 We're all human, we all make mistakes from time to time & we all have our moments - myself including 🙈 I often get emails from people saying they are too embarrassed to hit the gym or feel intimidated or etc – don't be! We all had to start somewhere & even us "fitness models" make dumbass mistakes from time to time. Learn from them, laugh at the growing pains & keep pushing forward. 😘
•••
Video 1: Back squatting 135lbs about 5 years ago, let the bar roll onto my neck, elbows came up tilting me even more forward as I drove up with my butt... The result is a face plant (100% ok after the fact) Oddly enough this is a weight I've done a few times prior without issue hence no spotter 🙈 This is now my warmup weight💪🏽
•••
Video 2: Doing a Crossfit WOD few years ago, kipping pull-ups with gloves on was a bad decision - bar slipped out of my hands - looks scary but I lucked out & walking away without any injury🙊
•••
Video 3: The right way to dump a failed squat 😏 I'm too short & squat lower than the safety bars so I have to step out - this time I thought I had 1 more in me in the set but was wrong. Shoot hips forward & let bar fall off your back 🤗
•••
Video 4: Making a fun ab workout video after a full body workout sometimes isn't the best of ideas - result: comical 😂
•••
Video 5: Form is everything - it's always the little things that make the biggest difference. Trying to rip the bar off the ground isn't as nearly as effective as having the proper technique 🤔
•••
In closing, never fear failure or looking silly from time to time - it happens to everyone! I have yet to meet a fitness model that hasn't made him or herself look like an idiot at some point 😂 #mondaymotivation #gymfail #gymfails #fitnessmotivation #motivational #motivation #gymaccident
